programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Aging 9-1-1
programme.desc: Joni, a hardworking 911 dispatcher on the night shift, struggles to keep up with her much younger-and much younger looking-husband. After she puts herself in expert hands for 10 days, will the new Joni wow her husband?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Heather Frederick
programme.desc: Heather Frederick isn't really as old as she appears. She's old before her time and it's up to Fiona and her team of experts to transform Heather from loveable granny to hot child in the city, in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Funny Girl
programme.desc: Growing up in a family of men, Beverly became one of the boys. Over the years she has struggled to find her own style, which has left her frustrated and ready for a change.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: New Mom, New Look
programme.desc: Cindy has an unusual family. Recently married to an older man, her stepchildren aren't much younger than she is. Her looks are failing her and Cindy now feels she no longer turns heads. Time to make Cindy look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA
programme.desc: Natasha has struggled to get her fashion jewelry business off the ground and lost sight of her own looks along the way. She worried that her tired looks and wardrobe of sweats were hurting sales in a business focused on fashion.
programme.sub-title: This Diva is Back and On Track

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Mirror, Mirror On The Wall
programme.desc: After losing 150 pounds, Angela has a new body, but she can't look in the mirror without noticing all her negative qualities. Cosmetic dentistry and Lasik surgery create a new look, but Angela is the only one who can fill the gap in her life.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Sizing Down And Looking Up
programme.desc: Allison has battled with her weight her entire life, and although she's lost 70 pounds through hard work and exercise, she still feels incredibly self-conscious about her appearance. Allison avoids certain social situations because of her insecurity.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Donna Fuller "One Year On"
programme.desc: Derby wife and mum Donna Fuller was stuck at home and stuck in a rut. Nicky revisits to see if Donna is still a woman who can pass the poll test and look 34.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding the Inner Girly Girl
programme.desc: Melissa Harris has devoted her life to raising her two young girls, but she's afraid she's falling short in her motherly duties. We're going to bring out the femme fatale in Melissa so she can be a super mom and role model.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back To Glamour
programme.desc: Rebecca gets a sophisticated makeover to bring back some of the glamour from her pre-mom days. Now, her husband can recognize the girl he married, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Fashion 911
programme.desc: Between two failed marriages, the loss of her father and caring for her ailing mother, Zoe feels life taking its toll on her appearance. She has found happiness in a new marriage, and she wants to feel confident when they are in public together.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Frizzy to Fine
programme.desc: Zina is a makeup artist by trade – a woman who encourages people to look their best to show off their spirit. However, spending all her time working and taking care of her children, Zina realizes she doesn't live by her own advice.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Emma Singh
programme.desc: Busy mum and part time student Emma Singh has a taste for the bad things in life and it shows big time on her face. Cosmetic surgeon Jan Stanek plans to get Emma to travel more lightly and youthfully by ridding Emma of her excess baggage on day one.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Viv Thomas
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 48 year old Viv Thomas.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New Year's Eve at Leopard's Den. Alice has returned, but the stress of combining work with caring for baby Bobby is causing tension between her and Danny. Liv is furious that Fatani hasn't told his mother about their relationship.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Scabby Monkey
programme.desc: Contending with overweight cats and their over protective owners was not what Danny Trevanion had in mind when he became a vet. So when a scruffy, barely alive African monkey arrives at his practise Danny is fascinated by the challenge.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: Danny is having second thoughts about the wisdom of uprooting his new family and ploughing all their money into a business venture that they know next to nothing about.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Work To Do
programme.desc: A successful giraffe capture means everyone is in high spirits, until the arrival of Evan and Olivia's real father, Simon, throws the family into turmoil.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Meerly Evan
programme.desc: Evan lets the mischievous meerkats loose in Rosie's room to cause havoc. Rosie is devastated when they destroy an irreplaceable photograph of her mother and rages at Evan. She decides once and for all to go back to Bristol.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Evan Meets Elli
programme.desc: Rogue young male elephants are rampaging through Leopard's Den and destroying everything the family have built, so Danny introduces a matriarch elephant in the hope that she will calm them down.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Dawn Feeling
programme.desc: At a typically rowdy family breakfast, Rosie is excitedly looking forward to the arrival of her friend Izzy, whilst Danny is concerned about the rumour of ivory poachers in the area. Unnoticed, Miranda the lion cub pads off into the bush.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Trevanions have been living at Leopard's Den for over a year. The wildlife is roaming freely and the family are settled into African way of life. Business however is not good. With an abundance of game lodges competition is fierce.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper team is responding to a life threatening emergency.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The team are called to a road accident where a woman has been cut from inside of her wrecked car.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: The team is responding to a life-threatening emergency. A cyclist in his 60s, Terrence Williams, is unresponsive and critical after an accident 15 minutes flying time from Auckland, near the small settlement of Maramarua.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The team are called out to a status 2 emergency; Clark Chamberlain was abseiling when he fell from the top of a cliff to the ground. He's now in a critical condition suffering from multiple injuries.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7
programme.desc: Young Rhys calls the embassy after his businessman father is arrested and jailed for fraud. Can Rhys raise the bail money to get him out of jail? It's a race against the clock.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Ash contacts the embassy convinced he's going to die after days of partying. The notorious Thai bucket strikes again! The embassy needs to uncover the truth. Is he really in danger or is he suffering from alcohol poisoning?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Nathan is in Phuket on a holiday of a lifetime, fuelled by sun, sex and steroids, when disaster strikes. 19-year-old Paris is on a gap year adventure of a lifetime. But just two months into her first-ever overseas holiday she's hit a big roadblock.

programme.title: Perfect Vagina
programme.desc: Through our author's personal journey this documentary will explore this fascinating secret world and question what or who is fuelling women's desire to have perfect vaginas.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: X-Raid Rally Dakar
programme.desc: Stéphane Peterhansel is the most successful driver in the history of the Dakar Rally. Along with the German team X-Raid he wins the 2012 and 2013 editions of this prestigious marathon in a Mini Countryman.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Ice Action Finland
programme.desc: Former World Rally Champion Armin Schwarz is a legend behind the wheels. Now he is instructing other talented people in driving a 300 hp Subaru WRX STI rally car on the snowy and icy, but also breathtaking landscape of Finland.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Racechip Challenge
programme.desc: More power and yet better fuel economy? With chip tuning this is supposed to be possible. We want to check this out and send two teams on a road trip with a difference. From Uhingen near Stuttgart in Germany, we travel to Barcelona and back.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: New Car Purchase Experience
programme.desc: A new car. A new driving experience. A new lifestyle. But which paths do four wheels, an engine and a whole lot of sheet metal take until the first drive? This is a question probably only asked by a few.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: 90 Years BMW Motor Bike
programme.desc: Precision, high-tech, high quality: After nine decades of eventful history ""BMW Motor Bikes"" are seen today are being almost too perfect. A story between tradition and innovation with ups and downs.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: The Car of the Future
programme.desc: The car of the future - this is how it might look: Aerodynamic, light and quiet. And with almost no fuel consumption. This is how we could soon travel on roads. But is a car like this just a pipe dream of engineers?

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Isle of Mann TT 2015 Documentary
programme.desc: The Tourist Trophy on the British Isle of Man is the most famous motorcycle race in the world. TT Sidecar champion Klaus Klaffenböck and racing expert Lenz Leberkern explore the fascination behind the TT Isle of Man.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Vintage Airplane Show Days
programme.desc: In this special report Motorvision TV will not be on tour on the streets, but in the air and will pay a tribute to the history of motorized aviation. One of the oldest airfields in Germany is located at Oberschleissheim near Munich.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Germany´s Supercar Rally
programme.desc: On Saturday the 11th of July 2015, owners and co-drivers of 450 supercars flocked at Germany's Bielefeld to join the biggest supercar rally ever organized in Europe so far.

programme.title: On Tour: Night of the Jumps
programme.desc: Munich, the Olympic Arena at the Night of the Jumps. These young guys will make the arena shake. They are fearless, and are going to really let it rip today. The biggest motor cross freestyle event in the world!

programme.title: On Tour: Bus Stunts with Action Concept
